  "body": "That method runs as a background task (via `asyncio.ensure_future()`) so it must catch and handle `OperationCancelled`, like, e.g., `_periodically_retry_timedout_and_missing()`\r\n\r\n```\r\n2018-08-09 18:49:29,637 ERROR: Task exception was never retrieved\r\nfuture: <Task finished coro=<StateDownloader._request_and_process_nodes() done, defined at /home/salgado/src/py-evm/trinity/sync/full/state.py:237> exception=OperationCancelled('Cancellation requested by ETHRequestResponseHandler:ETHPeer:PeerPool token',)>\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"/home/salgado/src/py-evm/trinity/sync/full/state.py\", line 239, in _request_and_process_nodes\r\n    node_data = await peer.requests.get_node_data(batch)\r\n  File \"/home/salgado/src/py-evm/trinity/protocol/eth/managers.py\", line 94, in __call__\r\n    return await self._request_and_wait(request, timeout)\r\n  File \"/home/salgado/src/py-evm/trinity/protocol/common/managers.py\", line 173, in _request_and_wait\r\n    return await self._wait_for_response(request, timeout=timeout)\r\n  File \"/home/salgado/src/py-evm/trinity/protocol/common/managers.py\", line 162, in _wait_for_response\r\n    response = await self.wait(future, timeout=timeout)\r\n  File \"/home/salgado/src/py-evm/p2p/cancellable.py\", line 19, in wait\r\n    return await self.wait_first(awaitable, token=token, timeout=timeout)\r\n  File \"/home/salgado/src/py-evm/p2p/cancellable.py\", line 41, in wait_first\r\n    return await token_chain.cancellable_wait(*awaitables, timeout=timeout)\r\n  File \"/home/salgado/virtualenvs/pyevm/lib/python3.6/site-packages/cancel_token/token.py\", line 150, in cancellable_wait\r\n    \"Cancellation requested by {} token\".format(self.triggered_token)\r\ncancel_token.exceptions.OperationCancelled: Cancellation requested by ETHRequestResponseHandler:ETHPeer:PeerPool token\r\n```",
